Dear all,

Any functor from a small category A to a complete category E induces a=20
contravariant adjunction between E and Set^A.  This in turn induces a=20
monad on E, the "codensity monad" of the functor.

(The construction of the adjunction is better known in its dual form,=20
starting with a functor from a small category to a COcomplete category.=20
For example, the usual functor from Delta into Top induces the usual=20
adjunction between topological spaces and simplicial sets.)

The codensity monad of the inclusion FinSet --> Set is the ultrafilter=20
monad.  This seems a rather basic fact, but I've been unable to find it i=
n=20
the literature.  I'd be grateful if someone could tell me a reference.

(I'm aware of the 1987 paper by Reinhard B=F6rger giving a different but=20
related characterization of the ultrafilter monad.)

Thanks,
Tom



